<item>
            <title>[QPID-206] Sending same TextMessage more than once causes text to be lost on second send</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-206</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Doing&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;msg = session.createTextMessage(&quot;msg&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
producer.send(msg);&lt;br/&gt;
producer.send(msg);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;will leave the second sent message without any content.  This is due to an error in the way the positions in the ByteBuffer are changed in getData()&lt;/p&gt;</description>
